cs.NI, cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.DC, cs.IT 

This paper discusses the use of SDN in networking, which falls under the category of Network and Internet Architecture (cs.NI). The paper also discusses the use of SDN for traffic engineering, which could fall under the category of Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) as well as Systems and Control (cs.SY). The paper proposes a new method of hybrid SDN/OSPF operation, which could fall under the category of Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing (cs.DC) as well as Information Theory (cs.IT).
